, Policy, and Civil Society demonstrates that the reach and significance of political ideology is best understood through a multidisciplinary approach. Contributors to this volume explore a broad territory from multiple perspectives: the influence of English country party ideology on late-eighteenth-century American political thought; multiculturalism, populism, and environmentalism in Canada; the ideological underpinnings of Canadian development assistance policy; contemporary efforts to shape working-class and farmer ideologies in western Canada; and the interweaving of academic theory and ideology in game theory. This stimulating volume offers empirical interpretations that break new ground, and demonstrates the strength of interdisciplinary approaches to the study of political ideology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIdeologyxPolitical aspectszCanada. 0aPolitical sciencezCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Parties.2bisacsh1 aAngus, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarney, Darin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobuzinskis, Laurent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJankovic, Ivan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaycock, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaycock, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLeier, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPilon, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReilly, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrand, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeldon, Steven, econtributor.4ctb